    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-12-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <head>114. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d114fn1"
                        >Source: National Security Council, Intelligence Files, 303 Committee
                        Meeting Minutes, 1969. Secret; Eyes Only. Copies were sent to Mitchell,
                            <persName corresp="#p_PDM1">Packard</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_HRM1"
                            >Helms</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-12-30">December 30, 1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Minutes of the Meeting of the 303 Committee, 23 December 1969</item>
                </list>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PRESENT</head>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>, Mr.
                            <persName>Mitchell</persName>, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                            >Johnson</persName>, and General Cushman</item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PDM1">Packard</persName> was out of the
                        city</item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName>John Hart</persName> was present for Item 1</item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName>William Nelson</persName> was present for Items 2 and
                        3</item>
                    <item>Mr. [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] was present for Item
                        4</item>
                    <item>Mr. [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] and Mr. [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] were present for Item 5</item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName>Archibald Roosevelt</persName> was present for Item 6</item>
                    <item>Mr. <persName>Thomas Karamessines</persName> and Mr. [<hi rend="italic"
                            >name not declassified</hi>] were present for all items</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of items 1–4, which are unrelated to the Soviet
                    Union.]</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">5. United States Government Support of Covert Action Directed
                        at the Soviet Union</hi>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>a.</label>
                    <item>The State Department memorandum for the 303 Committee dated 12 December
                        1969, entitled “U.S. Policy on Support for Covert Action Involving Emigrés
                        Directed at the Soviet Union,”<note n="2" xml:id="d114fn2">
                            <ref target="#d106">Document 106</ref>.</note> was approved as a basic
                        policy statement superceding <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5502/1,
                        dated 31 January 1955, entitled “U.S. Policy Toward Russian Anti-Soviet
                        Political Activities.”</item>
                    <label>b.</label>
                    <item>It was agreed that this policy statement will not be issued as a National
                        Security Directive Memorandum (<gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss>) but
                        will serve as the U.S. policy authorization for the kinds of émigré
                        activities described in the <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> paper dated
                        9 December 1969,<note n="3" xml:id="d114fn3">
                            <ref target="#d103">Document 103</ref>.</note> titled as in the above
                        paragraph heading.</item>
                    <label>c.</label>
                    <item>
                        <p>[<hi rend="italic">2 names not declassified</hi>] briefed the Committee
                            and responded to numerous questions on the following activities which
                            comprise the <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> covert action program
                            supporting media and contact activities aimed at stimulating and
                            sustaining pressures for liberalization and evolutionary change from
                            within the Soviet Union:</p>
                        <p>[<hi rend="italic">4 paragraphs (6 lines of source text) not
                                declassified</hi>]</p>
                    </item>
                    <pb facs="0380" n="347" xml:id="pg_347"/>
                    <label>d.</label>
                    <item>The Committee approved the continuation of the <gloss target="#t_CIA1"
                            >CIA</gloss> covert action program including the above individual
                        projects at the funding level contained in the <gloss target="#t_CIA1"
                            >CIA</gloss>
                        <gloss target="#t_FY1">FY</gloss> 1970 budget.</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to the Soviet Union.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Frank M. Chapin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
